{"/service/ndnp/gu/batch_gu_grouch_ver01/data/2022239691/00517010340/1923091701/0305.xml":{"full_text":"PAGE FOUR\n4 CORDELE DISPATCH\ni s wit Y eT Y\n.AND DAILY SENTINEL\n\nJasued Daily Except \u2018Saturday\nBY THE o\nDispatch Publishing \u20acompany.\n\nCHAS. E. BROWN, Editor,\nM\nws Subscription Price~\u2014Daily\nP' w\u2018ck SO BN NNNENBBNNS lzc\nP.' uonth :11'1.1.1..\u201c... \u2018sc\nTm\u2018 uumh. 1...-.....\u201c\u20181l \u2019l.\u201d\nm\u2018*m Wedsaue bil.fo'do'. '2.\u201c\nOne Year ........c.uvey.. $6,00\nG b /Semi-Weekly\nTm\u2018m\ufb02l\u2018 .--.-al'-.-... boe\nllg]lo BE i dvave dnsbkis $lBOO\n\"\u2018W, Y\u201c':\"o-t-onano-anc.. szooo\nEntered as second class matter\nJune 2nd, 1920, at the post office at\nCordele, Ga., under the Act of\nMarch Brd, 1879, i\nl\u201d\u2014._\u2014\u2014'-\u2014_\u2014\u2014-\u2014\u2014_-\u2014-\u2014\u2014\nThe Associated Press is exculsive:\nly entitled to the use for republica\n#ipn of all news dispatches credited\nto it or not otherwise credited in\nthis paper and also tke local news\npublished hereln.\nThe high-minded poor. ~and the\nright minded poor are the hope of\nthe nation. The rich have no real\n\u2018eause to worry. This isn\u2019t the day\nfor the poor man to lose heart.\nJohn Greer, seeretary of the\nCrisp County Board of Trade,\nrendered quite a bit of assistance\nin a farmers mneeting in Ocilla a\nwgek ago, if one must ju'dge from\n,the write up in the Ocilla Star of\nl\u2019ut week: Much development work\nis now under way in Irwin county.\ng i\nThe dairy farmers are to have in\nCordele a place where they can have\ntheir corn, velvet becans and hay\u2014\n_and all manner of dairy and chicken\nfecd ground for their stock and\npoultry. The Arabi Dairmen have\nb\u00e9en enjoying the use of ground\nfoed a long time and their testimony\nds to increased butter-fat s in\nteresting.\nThe editor of The Dispatch has\nan invitation from the Savannah\nBoard of Trade and the Savannah\nTri-State Exporition to attend press\nday festitives in Savannah on Sep\ntember 24 when the big Tri-State\nfair will be under way. Georgia\n;j\u2018gg_v_apm\u2019r people are to be guests\nof Savannah on that date. Cer\n\u2019t\ufb02nly, fine time is ahead for all\nwho_ attend,\nThe editor of The Dispatch has\nan invitation for today with the\nEleventh District Editors in their\nmecting in Valdosta. Judging from\nthe importance of the addresses by\nDan Bickers and Jack Williams, the\nefforts of President Ben T. Allon of\nthe association must be bearing\nfruit. The district conventions are\nbringing out newspaper develop\nment like nothing else we have ever\nseen at work :n Georgia.\nThe governor of Oklahoma has\nthe ire of the newspaper men up in\nhis eoffort to stop floggings in his\n\u2018gtate. We do not think newspaper\nmen are so far different from other\nmen as not to be answerable at\nsome point. The freedom of the\n\u2018press does not mean license to do\nwrong\u2014,nd the newspaper man\nwho stands boldly to block any\nman\u2019s effort to uproot lawlessness\nanywhere is doing wrong.\nGOOD DAIRY CATTLE\nI There is a great demand for good\nHairy cattle in this section\u2014a great\n\u2018demand. There will still be a\n.greater demand in the years ahead\nof us. The dairyman of today ought\nto eliminate the scrub sire in his\nherd and he ought to see that the\nscrub_goes out of the herd of his\nneighbor. \u2018That would make it pos\n_sible, for dairymen in Crisp county\nto say to the world that no scrub is\nheing offered forisal\u00e9,\ni 1 The truth about dairyilf:& today is\nthat there are very few cattle other\nthan herd culls offered for sale. We\nought to -produce good cattle, It\ncan be done with the circulating\npure bred sire scheme which is now\nbeing worked in Crisp county by\nl\u2019g\u00e9nj:s of the State College of Agri\n_culture and the United States De\n\u2018partment of Agriculture.\nIF IT WERE GOVERNOR GOR\nPON LEE i\nEditor Shope of the Dalton Citi\nzen writes fine things about Con\ngressman Gordon Less as timber\nfor governor of Georgia. We doubt\nnothing of that. Gordon Lee is a\ngood man\u2014one who would grace\nthe governor\u2019s office.\n\u2018But we are tninkit\\g of that At\nlanta bunch\u2014what ghall we call\nthem\u2014what name fits? If Gordon\nLee werg \ufb01gq_vqrnor of \u2018Georgia, thay\nwould pull him to pieces every thirty\nminutes. The. thing has been done\ntoo m\\nn}'; Eimes. And specially do\nwe remember what they did to\n\u201cUncle Nat Harris, ag worthy a son\nas ever bhore arms for the Confed\neracy\u2014possibly the last of the gray\nthat will ever hold this high office.\nHe wasn\u2019t from Atlanta, Gor\ndon Lee will have to move to At\ndanta #nd register his citizenship.\nHe will then have to stay long\nenough to become acclimated. That i\na requisite\u2014\u2014one which all men must\nhave or pay with their heads when\nthey go up from other points\u2014-like\nMonroe and Dalton and Macon and\nthe other metropolitain cen?\u00e9rs out\ngide of Atlanta.\nLet\u2019s be plain about it-\u2014one must\nhave the approval of the Atlanta\nlawyers who run state politics\u2014\nand then one must pass muster in\nthat mewspaper political writers or\nganization of which John Hammond\nis a persistant member. One must\npart his hair as they tell him\u2014must\nmake his office hours to accom\nmodate them, write his messages\nlike they say write them, and\u2014telk\nthe world he is from Atlanta.\nOh, boy! Gordon Lee has never\nstruck deep water till he tries to be\n\u2018governor without having Atlanta\n'approval\u2014and he doesn\u2019t get that\ntill the matter of citizenship in At\nlanta is determined. Let him try\nit\u2014without the moonshine liquor\nanZ his klansmen\u2019s badge and his\ncheap cheroots, If Georgians\u2014\nevery single voter of them outside\nof Atlanta\u2014were to back him, he\nwould find it rard to run the office\n\u2018if he were not an Atlantan first,\nlast and all the time. It takes that\nto make a successtul-g\u00e9vernor.\nTHE PINEARPLE PEAR\nThe following is from J. G.\nWoodruff, Horticulturists at the\nGeorgia Experiment Station:\n\u201cThis is a fruit best adapted to\nthe southern states, and promarily\nfor the Coastal Plain regions; that\nis, the region that includes the\neastern part of South Carolina, the\nlower half of Georgia, all of Florida\nand the lower parts of the states\nof Alabama, Mississippi, and Louisi\nana. The: |extensive planting of\nthis pear will be confined to this\nsection for \\itwo Treasons, First,\nbecause of the soil adaptability. A\ndeep, loose, porous soil is best suit\ned for it. While fertilization s\ncnecessar& the response. is not saq\nmarked as with most other fruits.\nThe clayey and rocky soils of the\nPiedmont and Appalachian regions,\nand further north, are not well suit\ned to the fruit. The pear likes an\nabundance of water, but it detests\n\u201cwet feet.\u201d\n\u201cThe second reason why this pear\nwill be confined to the southenra\nzone is because of the susceptabil\nity to late winter freezes. The tree\ngoes into the annual rest period\nearly in the fall, blooms out early in\nthe spring (by March Ist), grows\nrapidly, and iipens the fruit by\nAugust, \u2018When it is taken out of\nthe region outlined above, it is in\nserious\u2019! danger of sacrificing more\nthan half of the crops to late win\nter freezes,..\n\u201cAttempts are being made t\u00a2 in\ntroduces the pear into the r\u00e9gion\naround the Great Lakes, on the\nnorth side; but sufficient progress\nhas not yet been made to draw com\nclusive results. It is being tried in\nTexas with partial success; but\nprobably that region is lacking in\nsufficicnt moisture for the pear to\nthrive there. It is being experi\nmented with in the state of Oregon,\nwith almost failure. Nurserymen\nare propagating it in the state of\nTennessee, but no data is yet avail-'\nable, T\n\u201cThe trees skould be set forty]\n\u2018feet apart, preferably in checks, so\nas to admit cullivation in two direc\ntions, For the first four years the\npear orchard sheuld be -trained,\npruned, and cultivated similar an\nsapple orchard.. A mixture orchaxdi\nmay be cover cropped \u2018with cow\npeas and beans similar to a model\npecan orchard. Yt-is Dot Tecom:\nmended to sod tho \u2018pear orchard.\n\u201cIf one is planning to sct trevs of\nthis variety next fall, he should be\nsure that he gets trees of the\nPineapple Pear variety, that is, ac\ncept no substitute, whatever. There\nare only a fevk nurseries in the\nsouth that, are, as yet, propagating\nthe new variety (a list of these may\nbe had from the Georgia Experi\nment Station). If a nurseryman\nhas a pear that he-is in doubt about\nas to whether or not it is of this\nvariety and if he will send speciJ\nmens of the fruit and leaves to the\nGeorgia Experiment Station they\n\u201cwill be promptly identified.\u201d\nTHE EMBLEM OF COWARDICE\nWe hoticg that when three\nmasked Klansmen entered a\nchurch at Monroe, La., the oth\ner night, going up to give the\npastor some money, a doctor\nin the congregation arose and\ntore the rigging from their\nheads, and they lit out of the\nhouge carrying their money\nwith them. Well enough, Dis\nguised persons have no business\nin church or anywhere else in\ntende'd for a good mission.\nWhen appearing before the\npeople the Lord didn\u2019t come\nwith, His head 'covered up.\nThere was an organization of\nthis,kind in Pahlomegw recent\nly, intended for law and order.\n_Yet, several of the members are\nnow .foced with court trouble.\n\u2014Hahlonega Nugget.\nPeople representing any\ngood cause Gonot find it neces\nsary to cover their faces while\nin the performance of it. A\nmask is the emblem of\ncowardice.\u2014Daltqn Citizen,\nAnd the mask is not the only\nemblem of cowardice in the klan.\nWhen its membership starts out to\nrule, it sends 'a group\u2014a gang, we\nshould say\u2014to corner one poor\ndeyil and make him :their victim.\nThat\u2019s ecowardice, Real men be\nlieve in giving all individuals a\nfair showing. They even believe in\ngiving \u2018a dog an evem: start in\nfight.\nBE READY WITH CREAM\nThe creame'ry is going to be\nstarted in October. *He: ready\nwith some cream to make the\nday success.\u2014\nThomasville Times Enterprise.\nThat\u2019s the right advice\u2014and\nthen sgmehody make sure 'that\n\u2018there is some eream to be had, A\nsteady flow of it is the thing.\nThomasville will benefit only by\nthat, which is produced in the trade\nterritory surrounding. It may send\nfield men into territory of other\ncreameries. and at-great expense\nfor a time divert some cream, But\nthat\u2019s heading towards failure. The\ncreamery success will come from\ndairy development in Thomas coun\nty. That\u2019s the truth\u2014mo matter\nwho tries not to believe it.\nEvery south Georgia town the\nsize of Cordele or Thomasville\u2014\nought to have its modern creamery\nand storage facilities and\nits dairy interests in its adjacent\nterritory. Then south Georgia will\nprosper even faster than it has un~\nder all other intensified methods,\nTHIS IS A GOOD START\nLast Thursday Vadosta rais\ned forty thousand dollars for\nthe development of the dairy\ning \u2018industry in that section.\nFifteen thousand \u2018was raised\nfor the creamery and twenty\nfive thousand with which to buy\ncows.\u2014 Waycress Journal-Herald\n\u2014Wayecross Journal Herald,\nThis looks miore like dairy de\nvelopment than anything we have\nseen in recent weeks., We are\n''HE GORDELE DISPATCH\nauite ure that ths \u2018proportionate\ndistribution has beep made a cor\nrect onie, And in passing we should\nsay that, althcugh Crisp county has\nover fwemty-five hundred dairy eat-.\ntle today, it should spend forty\nthousand dollars before another\nthirty days are gone for more \u2018good\n\u2018cows,\nWe wish Valdosta great success.\nLet ev\u00e9ry center where a mnew\ncrealg\u2019bry is being built remember\nthat it is the dairy cow on the farm\nt.hat_ counts, Criecamery or no\ncreamery, the cow must be establish\ned on the farm where heretofore\nthere has been no cow. That is the\nsecrt, The creamery will take\n\u2018care\"{of itself 'if that program be\ncarri\u00e9d out.\n.DEAD MEN\u2019S TALES\nOmaha Wiorld Herald:\nHe ate everything his wife cooked.\nHe sald he would try anything once\n\u2018He blew out the gas.\nHe believed the label \u2018\u201cbottled in\nbond. 4? L\nHe didn\u2019t know she had g hushani\nHe found out it was a live wire.\nHe didn\u2019t stick \u2019em up guick enough\nHe rocked the hoat,\nHe was driving and -talking to the\ng\nHe was a road hog\nHe didn\u2019t know it was loaded.\nHe tried to beat the train to the\nicrossing,\nHe didn\u2019t see the otherrcar.\nH struck a match to see how much\ngas he had in the tank.\nHe called himself a journalist.\nHe was fond of whistling \u201cYes!\nWe Have No Bananas\u201d\u2019\nHe was a rpedestrlan who. didn\u2019t\nlstep guick enough, g\nHe had a habit of reading the sub\u2019\ntitles out loud at the movies,\nHe repeated the smart thing his\n,)aby said,\n\u201cHe\u2019bought his wife a revolver to\nshoot burglars with on nights when\nhe wag-out late,\nTHE SPIRITUAL IN PROSPERITY\nOcilla Star:\nIt wasva fact worthy .of special\nnote that the speakers at the farmers\nmeeting last \u2018Saturday afternoon in\nOcilla stressed the necessity of right\nliing as-a necessary prec\u00e9dent to a\nreturn of. prosperity, and that this\ngentiment: was cheered by the audi--\nence who had assembled to hear the,\nsuggestions of the men who had come\nto help \u2018show the way to i more sat\nisfactory ,-lblan of farming \u2018Mr.. Greer\u2019\nasserted that nothing\u2019would do more\nto bring back prosperity than a genu-:\nine revival of refigion among the peo\nple. Senator George'said that e\nfirmly believed that no people could\u2019\nprosper who trampled under foot the\nTen Commandments,\nMany expressions haye been heard\nfn the last few months to the effect\nthat the Almigthty is trying to bring\nthe peopel to their knees, and this\npaper seripusly believes that this is\ntrue. While not indfcting our people\nyet it can hardly be denied that God\nhas not been -taken into partnership\nin our business affairs as He hag a\u00b0\nright to expect, May it not be said\nthat most of us have said, if not in\nactual words, at least by our actions\n\u201cWe are going to succeed this year\nfa spite of God?\u2019\u2019 Have we done 50?2\u2019\nNc need io answer.\n\u2018We noedj a new partner in our busi\nnesses. Shell' God be taken into \u2018our\nnext year's plans.\nPersons may eat toadstools and\nyet live, thanks to a medical dis\ncovery mow being perfected inm\nFrance. A horse was immunized by\nsuccessive injections of poisonous\nmusroonrs, The setum made from\nthe animal was tried successfully\non mice and rabbits who had b';e;\u00e9n.\nfed the'desdly amainta mushroom.\nMIDNIGHT SLRVICE\nTHAT SATISTIES\nHOT WEINERS, COLD\nDRINKS, CIGARS, Etc.\nSTOP WITH US FOR A\nQUICK AND APPETIZ.\nING LUNCH.\nBARWICK\u2019S\nLUNCHSTAND\nEIGHTH STREET SOUTH\ns\nListen to This!\nWe enly want to remind yod\nthat we de =zuto repairing, ra\ndiator repairing, uet\ufb02ene gas\nwelding \u2018of 'a \u2018dependable Kind\nfor live and let live prices.\nLet us show you.\nBobertsom Ol Stand\nPHONE 157-W\nJ-\\E m\u00dfg y ng!o 3\nCORDELE, GEORGIA\nettt et\n\u2018Arrival \u2018and Departure of Passenger\nTrains, >crdele Union Depot.\neet e\nThe following schedule figures\nlshed umtp,rrfu'jom Van pub-\nAtlantg, .lr-n\u2018\ufb01' m Atm' He\nArrives\u2014 \u201c\u2014Departs\n4:4oam Atlunts-Blrm'l,nJhnn_ :30am\nIZ:3oam: Wayeross. Brunswick \u2018wg\ns2pm Atlanta 45pm\u2019\n12:30am llou\\lme-i\u2018hat;pvmo 43{::,\n2:35pm Fitzgerald-Waycross 3 )bpm-\nGeoruia Bonthwestern snd Gulf M. I,\nLeave Zofw- \u00ab\u2014Arrive /\u00a5From!\n#:9oam Albany Loeal 7:3opm\na:gspm Al}\\;luny-'fhomuv\u2018lllo v:::Bpm\n4:99pm Albany-Moultrie, L2:Bspm\n\u2018i\ufb02\u2019g